PHILLIPS PETROLEUM COMPANY v. FEDERAL POWER COMMISSION. No. 7022. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Sept. 13, 1962. Lloyd G. Minter, Kenneth Heady and John R. Rebman, Bartlesville, Okl., for petitioner. Richard A. Solomon, Gen. Counsel, Howard E. Wahrenbrock, Solicitor, and Josephine H. Klein, Atty., Federal Power Commission, Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before PHILLIPS, PICKETT and HILL, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Proceeding transferred September 13, 1962, to United States Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit.
